"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Code Simplification: Kiro Agent Integration\n\n## Context\n\nThe `alisha/kiro-oneshot` branch adds a full Amazon Kiro IDE agent integration (~5,700 lines across 28 files). Two DRY violations were found in the new Kiro agent code that increase maintenance surface without adding value:\n\n1. **4x repeated transcript read+parse pattern** in `kiro.go` — four public methods duplicate the same file read, error check, and parse logic\n2. **3x repeated command prefix computation** in `hooks.go` — three functions compute the identical `cmdPrefix` from a `localDev` bool\n\nAll other code on this branch was reviewed and found to be clean — no further simplifications are warranted. (The `map[string]bool` for the `seen` set in `transcript.go` matches the project convention of 63 occurrences; `ChunkTranscript` error wrapping is required by `wrapcheck` linter.)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Extract `readAndParseTranscript` helper (`kiro.go`)\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/kiro.go`\n\nAdd a private sentinel error and helper function before `GetTranscriptPosition` (~line 166):\n\n```go\nvar errTranscriptEmpty = errors.New(\"transcript is empty or missing\")\n\nfunc readAndParseTranscript(path string) (*kiroTranscript, error) {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n    if err != nil {\n        if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n            return nil, errTranscriptEmpty\n        }\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading transcript: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if len(data) == 0 {\n        return nil, errTranscriptEmpty\n    }\n    t, err := parseTranscript(data)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing transcript: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return t, nil\n}\n```\n\nRefactor these 4 methods to use it:\n- `GetTranscriptPosition` — check `errors.Is(err, errTranscriptEmpty)` → return `0, nil`\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — check `errors.Is(err, errTranscriptEmpty)` → return `nil, 0, nil`\n- `ExtractPrompts` — propagate error directly (no special handling for empty)\n- `ExtractSummary` — propagate error directly\n\n**Net impact:** ~-20 lines, eliminates 4 copies of the read+parse boilerplate.\n\n### 2. Extract `hookCmdPrefix` helper (`hooks.go`)\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go`\n\nAdd a private helper near the other unexported functions (~line 215, after `hasEntireHook`):\n\n```go\nfunc hookCmdPrefix(localDev bool) string {\n    if localDev {\n        return localDevCmdPrefix + \"hooks kiro \"\n    }\n    return prodHookCmdPrefix\n}\n```\n\nReplace the 5-line `if/else` block with a single line in:\n- `InstallHooks` (line 84)\n- `allHooksPresent` (line 192)\n- `allIDEHooksPresent` (line 271)\n\n**Net impact:** ~-7 lines, consolidates 3 copies of the same logic.\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/kiro.go` | Add `errTranscriptEmpty` + `readAndParseTranscript`; refactor 4 methods |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` | Add `hookCmdPrefix`; refactor 3 call sites |\n\nNo test files need modification — all existing tests validate the same behavioral contracts.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nAll existing tests for `GetTranscriptPosition`, `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`, `ExtractPrompts`, `ExtractSummary`, `InstallHooks`, `allHooksPresent`, and `allIDEHooksPresent` must pass unchanged.\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/c180cd4e-50b8-48fb-8ea6-bb97c9341d8f.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncommit"